<view isVisible="false" template="dashboard.html" stylesheet="custom.css,health_checks.css">
  <label>Home</label>

  <pattern name="nav" layoutPanel="appHeader" />

  <module name="Search" layoutPanel="panel_row1_col1">
    <param name="search"><![CDATA[
| rest /services/apps/local splunk_server=local
| search title="cisco_cdr"
| fields title label author version description
| stats last(*) as *
| rex field="version" mode="sed" "s/(\d+\.\d+)\.0/\1/"
    ]]></param>
    <module name="HTML" layoutPanel="viewHeader">
      <param name="html"><![CDATA[
        <h1>Welcome to Cisco CDR Reporting and Analytics $results[0].version$</h1>
      ]]></param>
    </module>
  </module>

  <module name="URLLoader" layoutPanel="viewHeader">
    <param name="keepURLUpdated">True</param>
    <!--
      Overall flow chart for "customer did it wrong."

      1) SPLUNK TOO OLD.
        Customer installs Cisco CDR on Splunk 7.3,  or upgrades old Cisco CDR to latest on 7.3
        a)  home_redirect.xml is a simplexml page. It runs some JS in dashboard.js, displays a
            message that they need at least Splunk 8.X now.

        b)  If they go to a bookmark right to a canary URL... cisco_cdr_shunt has been modified
            in Cisco CDR 6.5 to redirect to home_redirect (thus GOTO 1a above)

        c)  If they go to a bookmark right to an advanced XML URL...
            application.js has a tiny thing that redirects to /app/cisco_cdr (thus GOTO 1a)

      2) CANARY MISSING ENTIRELY
         Customer didn't notice the thing about Canary. Canary is not installed at all.
         a) home_redirect is a simplexml page for this reason. It runs some JS in dashboard.js,
            makes a rest call to see if Canary is there.
            If it's not, displays a message that Canary is needed.

      For the next three see /appserver/static/lib/check_status.js  but here's the short version.
      3) JS on all pages checks the license status.
         if no license is found, on the homepage messaging takes over the page and no further checks happen.
         other pages (with some exceptions eg the update_license page) redirect to the homepage.

      4) IF a license is found, then JS on the homepage in particular runs a tstats summariesonly
         search, to see if any cucm_cdr data is indexed, in any index.  It displays a big message if not.

      5) if neither of those do anything (courtesy of some css logic in custom.css),
         then we proceed to this next important business,

      6) is there any data indexed in the `custom_index`
         technically this and #7 (the health checks) run in parallel, but if this one fails it supercedes
         and hides all other content on the page.
         see appserver/static/lib/check_status.js - it runs a search and if 0 results come back it puts
         the whole page into a css state called "noDataIndexed"

      7) "Do any critical health checks fail?"


      KNOWN FLAWS:
      - if Canary is there but very old, cisco cdr python may fail unpredictably.
        currently cisco_cdr_shunt does not check whether canary version is >= what app.conf specifies
        as minimum version.   It effectively hopes that canary can run *enough* to get to the
        health check...
      - 1c not covered by any testing.
      - 1b *can* be manually verified. See comment on TestShuntEndpoint

    -->
    <module name="Search" layoutPanel="panel_row2_col1">
      <param name="search"><![CDATA[
| rest /servicesNS/-/-/configs/conf-checklist splunk_server=local
| rename eai:appName as app search as searchToRun
| fields app title searchToRun drilldown
| search app="cisco_cdr" title="critical_*"
| eval drilldownLabel=if(isnull(drilldown),"see health check results","run troubleshooting search")
| eval drilldown=if(isnull(drilldown),searchToRun,drilldown)
      ]]></param>

      <module name="HTML">
        <param name="html"><![CDATA[
          <strong>You appear to have some CDR data indexed. However one or more critical health checks have failed and should be addressed as soon as possible:</strong>
        ]]></param>
      </module>

      <module name="Pager">

        <module name="Multiplexer">
          <param name="fields">app,searchToRun,drilldown,drilldownLabel</param>

          <module name="Search">
            <param name="search">$searchToRun.rawValue$ | sort - severity_level |  table severity_level metric</param>

            <module name="ProgressIndicator"/>

            <module name="HTML">
              <param name="html"><![CDATA[
               <p class="checklistConfSeverity$results[0].severity_level$" style="margin-bottom:0px;">
                  $results[0].metric$<br>
                  Please go to "Admin > Run health checks" to get more detailed information.
                </p>
              ]]></param>
              <param name="customBehavior">setPageStateIfCriticalHealthCheckFailed</param>
            </module>

          </module>
        </module>
      </module>
    </module>



    <module name="NullModule" layoutPanel="mainSearchControls">

      <pattern name="call_filter_controls">

        <module name="Button">
          <param name="label">go</param>

          <module name="Redirector">
            <param name="url">calls</param>
            <param name="arg.numberType">$numberType.rawValue$</param>
            <param name="arg.number">$number.rawValue$</param>
            <param name="arg.data_type">$data_type.rawValue$</param>
            <param name="arg.earliest">$search.timeRange.earliest$</param>
            <param name="arg.latest">$search.timeRange.latest$</param>
            <param name="arg.type">$type.rawValue$</param>
          </module>
        </module>
      </pattern>



    </module>










